##########To copy a file from our local machine to remote machine command is 

scp -i /path/to/local/file /path/to/local/file username@remote_host:/path/to/destination/

########for example to copy a file use below reference

 scp -i C:\Users\Dell\OneDrive\Desktop\awskeypairs\mvn-pair.pem C:\Users\Dell\OneDrive\Desktop\awskeypairs\mvn-pair.pem root@3.111.38.210:/home/ubuntu

#########change the filename and path of the keypair file and user 

#############If you are logged in as a normal user and want to copy a file to a root-owned directory:

sudo cp /home/ubuntu_user/file.txt /root/

############sudo gives temporary root privileges.
############/root/ is the home directory of the root user.
